Our goal is to be able to pass in a filter criteria in the URL. This is to support proper back button behaviour. We are using UI Router but I think this requirement is fairly generic.

To get this working we've created an alternative st-search directive that just does a one way transfer from model to the table state, and it is working fine for us. However, we get multiple calls to the st-pipe function on page load. Once with empty filter and then another when the model is modified.

We're open to using a different approach, but we like using ng-model to hold the filter, because we can then watch for changes in the controller, etc. I think the model <--> table state sync was mentioned in another issue.

Our directive looks like this:
```
angular.module('smart-table')
.directive("stSearch2", ['stConfig', '$timeout', '$log', function(stConfig, $timeout, $log) {
        return {
            require: '^stTable',
            scope: {
                predicate: '=?stSearch2',
                ngModel: '='
            },
            link: function(scope, element, attr, ctrl) {
                var tableCtrl=ctrl;
                var throttle = attr.stDelay || stConfig.search.delay;

                // model -> table state
                scope.$watch('ngModel', function(newVal) {
                    if ( newVal ) {
                        $log.info("Model changed for search!!", scope.predicate, newVal);
                        tableCtrl.search(newVal, scope.predicate || '');
                    }
                });
            }
        }
    }]);
```

You can see example Plunkr here: http://plnkr.co/edit/FErRR0cgvdBduo94fYca?p=info. In the console you will see "func called" twice on page load.

Any help much appreciated.

